Here’s what is documented about training filesystem paths and directory structure instead:
- Training job contents are packaged from your local directory and copied into the container at the root of the base image’s working directory (path not specified). Source: `https://docs.baseten.co/training/concepts/basics`
- Cache mounts:
  - Project cache: `/root/.cache/user_artifacts` via `$BT_PROJECT_CACHE_DIR`
  - Team cache: `/root/.cache/team_artifacts` via `$BT_TEAM_CACHE_DIR`
  - SDK reference also lists `/root/.cache/huggingface` and `$BT_RW_CACHE_DIR` as cache locations
  Source: `https://docs.baseten.co/training/concepts/cache`, `https://docs.baseten.co/reference/sdk/training`
- Checkpoint directory: `$BT_CHECKPOINT_DIR`, example path `/mnt/ckpts` (used for automatic checkpointing). Source: `https://docs.baseten.co/reference/sdk/training`, `https://docs.baseten.co/training/concepts/checkpointing`

If you’re expecting `/mnt/code`, it may be an internal or older path not reflected in current public docs. If you have a specific Baseten doc or example that mentions `/mnt/code`, send it over and I can reconcile it with the current documentation.
